data.name: Cinnamon
data.description: Rajput architecture, magnificence and sumptuousness - this is the essence that pervades Cinnamon, originally the erstwhile dining room of the Prime Minister of Jaipur State Cinnamon is a gourmet theatre endearing the many faces of Indian cuisine from four Princely States of India – Rajputana, Awadh, Hyderabad and Kashmir. The restaurant showcases the true worth of our love for the age old culinary art through its contemporary styling and artistic ways. It was an instinct to discover the pleasure of creating perfection that drove us to a yearning to put together a repertoire of simple dishes to give us a place on the global culinary map. The journey takes a swirl through the “Bajot”, a unique private dining area in the restaurant, wherein our esteemed guests are treated to a special chef’s menu, pampered by our highly trained servers and chef-in-charge himself. The menu showcases dishes made to order and proves to be a boon for connoisseurs of food. Redefining Indian food, decor and the service a class apart, our menu uses the freshest of ingredients, authentic herbs and whole spices to create a modest twist in the traditional cuisines from the Princely States of India. Allow us to use a teaspoon of cinnamon or a strand of saffron or slivers of almonds and pistachio to entice you and delight you with wisps of the aromas from the different regions of India. We trust you will enjoy the experience and explore your gourmet senses. So pamper your taste buds and relish the ever enthusiastic journey, where you will accidently stumble upon the good life of savouring food, flavours, spices and exploring wines.

data.name: Baluchi
data.description: Baluchi, A signature pan Indian destination has set the bar when it comes to authentic Indian curries and meats, marinated with rare herbs and exotic spices. A special attraction of the restaurant is the Naanery i.e. The bread bar offering a selection of artisanal breads baked the classic Indian way in an iron tandoor instead of the universally used clay tandoor and served along with a variety of homemade chutneys made with our special in-house recipes that have evolved over the years. The Restaurant also offers great collection of old and new world wines, that can be paired with the bread & chutney combination for an authentic Baluchi Rhapsody! Those rushed for time can go for the Express Lunch Thali.

data.name: The Great Kabab Factory
data.description: For mouthwatering flavours of India, try one of the area's top Indian restaurants at this hotel's location in Jaipur. The Great Kabab Factory features an open kitchen area, where expert chefs prepare tasty kababs in full view, providing guests with a feast for the eyes, nose and mouth as the sights, aromas and flavours combine for true one-of-a-kind dining experiences. A factory-like ambience gives the restaurant a contemporary feel as you start with a salad, followed by six varieties of kababs, served one after another to keep your taste buds tantalized. Have chilled chhaas, raitas, two varieties of dals vegetable gravy or non-vegetable curry and biryanis. You can also indulge in an exotic dessert and a liquor concoction to enhance your dining experience. The Great Kabab Factory is open for only dinner seven days a week. Guests are encouraged to reserve tables in advance to avoid inconvenience.
